<SECOND>PM-Channel Glide,0426</SECOND>
<UNK>Briton Claims Record As First Woman To Cross English Channel By Hang
Glider</UNK>
<DATELINE>DOVER, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A Briton has claimed a place in the record books as the first woman to cross the English Channel by hang glider, making the 21-mile trip to <LOCATION> France </LOCATION> in 22 minutes. Strapped into her frail craft, 29-year-old <PERSON> Judy </PERSON> <PERSON> Leden </PERSON> was first lifted to 13,500 feet over <LOCATION> Dover </LOCATION> by a hot air balloon Wednesday morning. The balloon's pilot, <PERSON> Ron </PERSON> <PERSON> Griffin </PERSON>, then cut the rope on which the hang glider was suspended 30 feet below his craft, sending the glider into a spinning 200-foot nose dive before it leveled out and began its downward glide. Miss <PERSON> Leden </PERSON> came down on a beach at Le Chatelet midway between the <LOCATION> French </LOCATION> north coast ports of <LOCATION> Calais </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Boulogne </LOCATION>. After landing, she admitted to being scared at the start of the flight: `` It was the highest I had ever been with a hang glider so I was going into the unknown. `` I am not frightened very easily but I was terrified for a short time. Because of the thinness of the air at 13,000 feet I went to at least 110 degrees and was rotating very fast, which is the way the hang glider recovers and begins to fly. `` I kept my nerve ... but once that horrible moment was over I had a lovely smooth glide over to <LOCATION> France </LOCATION>.'' Preparations for the flight, which was sponsored by an auto company, were dogged by technical problems for a year. But Miss <PERSON> Leden </PERSON> said Wednesday's crossing was `` incredibly smooth, without any serious complications.'' Miss Leden, from <LOCATION> Derbyshire </LOCATION> in northern <LOCATION> England </LOCATION>, holds the women's world open distance hang gliding record of 145.34 miles. That flight, listed in the Guinness Book of Records, was between <LOCATION> Nevada </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> over <LOCATION> Owens </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION> on July 13, 1983. She was honored by Queen <PERSON> Elizabeth </PERSON> <PERSON> II </PERSON> this year by being made a Member of the Order of the British Empire in recognition of her services to the sport. British news reports said the only other hang glider pilot to fly across the English Channel was Briton <PERSON> Ken </PERSON> <PERSON> Messenger </PERSON> in 1977. He suffered frostbite because of cold at the high altitude from which he started. <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Civil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aviation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Authority </ORGANIZATION> said in a statement after <PERSON> Miss </PERSON> <PERSON> Leden </PERSON>'s crossing Wednesday that for safety reasons it will not allow any further hang gliding attempts across the English Channel. The skies above the Channel are a major commercial air route.
