<HEAD>EDS: Retransmitting to include slug</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By KIM I. MILLS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 FOOD for <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION>, a pet charity of a former top official at the <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Housing </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Urban </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Development </ORGANIZATION>, has raised thousands of dollars without proper registration in several states, according to records. A check by The <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> of the offices of state attorneys general and other agencies regulating charities found FOOD is not registered in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Louisiana </LOCATION>, the <LOCATION> District </LOCATION> <LOCATION> of </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Columbia </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Colorado </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> or its home state of <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION>. The organization raised at least $ 580,000 from 1986 to 1988, much of it in those states, and half of that came from individuals or firms known to be involved with <ORGANIZATION> HUD </ORGANIZATION> programs, according to an internal agency report released in April. `` I was told we did n't have to have a license,'' <PERSON> Vasilios </PERSON> <PERSON> Damavolites </PERSON>, FOOD's treasurer, said in an interview from <LOCATION> Novi </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mich. </LOCATION>, where the organization is headquartered. <PERSON> Damavolites </PERSON>, who is president of <ORGANIZATION> Dial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Construction </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and goes by the anglicized name of <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Damas </PERSON>, said contributions have been difficult to raise since the release of a <ORGANIZATION> HUD </ORGANIZATION> report that touched on the organization and its links to former agency official <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PER