ved to <ORGANIZATION> HUD </ORGANIZATION> as assistant secretary for housing, according to the report. The report said <PERSON> Demery </PERSON> continued to work for the charity, attending at least eight fund-raisers in the 20 months after he became assistant secretary. A check of <PERSON> Demery </PERSON>'s phone logs, obtained under the Freedom of Information Act, revealed that <PERSON> Demery </PERSON> often spoke to FOOD officials during working hours. After the investigation, <ORGANIZATION> HUD </ORGANIZATION> Inspector General <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Adams </PERSON> concluded that <PERSON> Demery </PERSON> may have violated the department's standards of conduct, which prohibit employees from directly or indirectly soliciting anything of value from anyone with `` interests that may substantially be affected'' by <ORGANIZATION> HUD </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Demery </PERSON> says the conclusions were based on circumstantial evidence, and says he never asked for contributions from any <ORGANIZATION> HUD </ORGANIZATION> developer. FOOD for <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> at one time held a license to solicit contributions in its home state of <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION>, but allowed it to lapse in September 1987, according to documents obtained from the <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION> attorney general. A reapplication made this year has been delayed until FOOD can provide notarized signatures of two officers, the documents show. Yet FOOD held two fund-raisers in <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION> in 1988 and 1989, the organization's treasurer said in a telephone interview this week. FOOD also held at least 10 fundraising events in six other states and the <LOCATION> District </LOCATION> <LOCATION> of </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Columbia </LOCATION> in 1987 and 1988, according to the <ORGANIZATION> HUD </ORGANIZATION> audit. FOOD also filed papers with the <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION> attorney general in June saying that it had `` pending applications in other states'' for licenses, although <PERSON> Damas </PERSON> said he did not know which states.
