<HEAD>Northrop Division Temporarily Suspended By Air Force</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A division of the <ORGANIZATION> Northrop </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> wo n't be allowed to do business with the government because of alleged fraud connected to two weapons systems the division worked on. Precision Product Division of <LOCATION> Norwood </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mass. </LOCATION>, was suspended temporarily because of criminal charges brought last spring over the division's work on the flight data transmitter for the air-launched cruise missile and a stabilization system for the <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION>'s AV-8B Harrier jet, <ORGANIZATION> Northrop </ORGANIZATION> said Wednesday. The suspension is temporary pending completion of the legal proceedings, according to the <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> letter informing <ORGANIZATION> Northrop </ORGANIZATION> of the suspension. The letter, obtained by The <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION>, said the indictment returned in the federal court in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> alleged <ORGANIZATION> Northrop </ORGANIZATION> and others `` conspired to defraud the government by knowingly supplying untested and out-of-specification flight stabilization and control packages and making false, fictitious and fraudulent statements and representations'' regarding the cruise missile and the Harrier jet. The suspension involves only future business at Precision Products, not contracts elsewhere at <ORGANIZATION> Northrop </ORGANIZATION> or contracts at Precision on which work is now underway. The company said the division accounts for about 2 -LCB- percent of sales and less than 4 percent of its $ 5 billion order backlog. <ORGANIZATION> Northrop </ORGANIZATION> is a major defense contractor, building the new B-2 `` stealth'' bomber. <ORGANIZATION> Northrop </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Loye </PERSON> <PERSON> Miller </PERSON> called the government's charges `` unwarranted and exaggerated,'' and the suspension `` unnecessary.'' `` The company intends to provide information in opposition to the government's temporary suspension of the unit,'' the statement said. <ORGANIZATION> Northrop </ORGANIZATION>'s statement said the company has taken `` strong actions'' to assure that it is a responsible contractor, including the closure of a facility in <LOCATION> Pomona </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, and the dismissal of several employees.
