<DATELINE>BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An 8-year-old Hungarian girl's dream of meeting President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> came true today at <LOCATION> Ferihegy </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION>, where she chatted with the tall, lanky American and gave him a mop-haired doll. With an assist from a local children's TV show and the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Embassy </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Nicoletta </PERSON> <PERSON> Nikolaibisz </PERSON> met <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> on the airport runway just before he flew to <LOCATION> Paris </LOCATION> after a two-day visit to <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> leaned over and listened to <PERSON> Nicoletta </PERSON> talk as he gently shook her gift of a doll with blue, mop-like hair and a blue dress. She expressed her wish to meet <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> when she wrote a letter asking to appear on `` Three Wishes,'' a popular Hungarian TV show for children. `` The girl said she would like to meet the president, and that was worked into the -LRB- <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>'s -RRB- official program,'' said <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Embassy press attache <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> McCarthy </PERSON>. <PERSON> Nicoletta </PERSON> will appear on the `` Three Wishes'' show in September.
