<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Barbara </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>, taking time out Thursday from the festive French bicentennial celebration, inaugurated a wing at the American Hospital with an extemporaneous speech _ an informal touch recently adopted by the first couple. `` I had a long speech here but I learned something from my husband,'' Mrs. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> told the audience as she tore up her prepared remarks. President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> had done the same in <LOCATION> Budapest </LOCATION> on Tuesday as a courtesy to the crowd standing in the rain. Mrs. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> opened the new <LOCATION> Florence </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Gould </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Pavilion </LOCATION> and high-tech medical center at the hospital, which is located in a posh Parisian suburb. `` This is the most wonderful thing that's ever happened to me,'' she said. `` You've stretched my life a little bit. I'm on a plaque.'' The plaque, which notes the inauguration, will be hung at the hospital. The <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hospital </ORGANIZATION>, which Mrs. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> toured for 30 minutes, includes the new <ORGANIZATION> C.V. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Starr </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Medical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the first facility in <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> with a communications network for teaching and diagnostics link directly to the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. Before leaving the podium, Mrs. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> bent down to shake the hands of four children, out-patients at the facility, who presented her with a silver cup and a spiral-notebook style cookbook written by Americans living in <LOCATION> Paris </LOCATION>. Earlier, Mrs. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> joined her husband and about 30 world leaders at a reading of the Declara