 City officials who tried to block a Pink Floyd concert for fear the loud music would damage historic buildings relented Thursday after the British rockers agreed to keep the volume down. Organizers of the weekend concert agreed also to move the floating stage in the <LOCATION> Venice </LOCATION> lagoon farther from St. <PERSON> Mark </PERSON>'s piazza than planned, city officials said. The top volume will be cut to 60 decibels from 105 decibels. The Jericho scenario was raised by city preservation officials, who threatened Wednesday to deny permission for the concert. The concert Saturday is free, and spectators are expected to watch from boats, rooftops and the shore.
