 Force </ORGANIZATION> was concerned. No first flight is anticipated Friday because the crew and the pilots needed rest, the general said. The flying wing was decked out with orange highlights that were used to cover sensors and test equipment. On Monday, the gray bomber built from composite materials rather than metal conducted slow-speed tests on the ground, achieving a speed of approximately 102 mph. In <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> on Thursday, <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> Secretary <PERSON> Dick </PERSON> <PERSON> Cheney </PERSON> pleaded with <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> not to `` nickel and dime to death'' the B-2, saying the stealth bomber is essential for <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> capability to `` penetrate improving Soviet air defenses.'' Testifying before the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Armed </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Cheney </PERSON> urged lawmakers to try to overcome `` sticker shock'' at the $ 500 million to $ 750 million price for each plane and to restore some $ 800 million the panel cut from the B-2 budget last month. Lawmakers warned <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> officials earlier this week that the B-2 faces a tough uphill fight in <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> despite the warplane's strategic importance `` Put it in perspective or there's a real possibility that the B-2 will become a museum piece,'' Rep. <PERSON> Les </PERSON> <PERSON> Aspin </PERSON>, D-Wis., chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Armed </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION>, told <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> officials at the start of a hearing The <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> campaign comes amid growing opposition to the bomber, which recent estimates indicate would be the most expensive aircraft in history. The <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION> announced last week the first flight tests of the bomber, which are 18 months behind schedule, would be held during the next two weeks. The Pentagon is proposing a $ 4.7 billion budget in fiscal 1990 for the B-2. The plane will cost about $ 24 billion over a three-year peak period beginning in fiscal 1992, according to <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> figures. The department has invested about $ 22.4 billion in the plane so far.
