<HEAD>London Shares Weaker At Midday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Share prices were weaker but off their minimum levels around midday Thursday, as profit-taking crept into the market before the end of the current two-week trading account on Friday. <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> divides trading into two-week and three-week trading periods for accounting purposes. Dealers said there was n't any concerted selling pressure. `` You'd have to be a fool to take a short -LRB- position -RRB- with all the bids on the table at the moment, and the possibility of a few more,'' one market maker said A host of rumors were making the rounds, highlighting a number of stocks, dealers said. At about noon, the <ORGANIZATION> Financial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times-Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> 100-share index was 7.6 points, or 0.3 percent, weaker at 2,249.1, just a shade below its best level for the day of 2,249.4. The index sunk as low as 2,242.9 during the morning before rebounding to its current level. Volume amounted to a moderate 318.4 million shares at midday compared with 539.1 million shares at the same time Wednesday.
