<FIRST>r f BC-Britain-Unemployment     07-13 0101</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Unemployment,0107</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rate Falls to 6.3 Percent, Lowest Rate in Nearly Nine Years</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>'s unemployment rate fell to a seasonally adjusted 6.3 percent in June from 6.4 percent in May, the government said Thursday. The latest rate was the lowest since October 1980, and compared with 8.1 percent in June 1988, the Department of Employment said. The number of jobless people fell 26,500. The financial markets had expected a 30,000 drop. The number of unemployed, without seasonal adjustment, was 1.74 million people in June, compared with a 1.80 million in May and 2.34 million a year ago.
</TEXT>
