the arrangements made in February. `` We are delighted that negotiations were resumed and that they have resulted in a transaction in line with the original terms,'' said <ORGANIZATION> Unilever </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Angus </PERSON>. `` Faberge will be an excellent fit with <ORGANIZATION> Unilever </ORGANIZATION>'s existing personal products operations and <PERSON> Elizabeth </PERSON> <PERSON> Arden </PERSON> furthers our ambition to be strongly represented in the important prestige skin-care, color cosmetics and fragrance sectors,'' he said. Under the contract, <ORGANIZATION> Unilever </ORGANIZATION> is to buy all of Faberge except for the <ORGANIZATION> McGregor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Apparel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION>, which comprises clothing lines such as Botany 500, Wonderknit and <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> the Kid. <PERSON> Faberge </PERSON>, bought by the <PERSON> Riklis </PERSON> group in 1984 for about $ 180 million, is a well known manufacturer of personal care products, including hair sprays, shampoos, deodorants and fragrances. Among Faberge's brand names are Aqua Net and Brut. <PERSON> Elizabeth </PERSON> <PERSON> Arden </PERSON> makes an assortment of premium skin care products, perfumes and makeups marketed under the names <PERSON> Elizabeth </PERSON> <PERSON> Arden </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Lagerfeld </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Fendi </PERSON> and <PERSON> Chloe </PERSON>. New York-based <PERSON> Riklis </PERSON>, whose other holdings include <ORGANIZATION> Samsonite </ORGANIZATION> luggage and <ORGANIZATION> Culligan </ORGANIZATION> water softeners, acquired <PERSON> Elizabeth </PERSON> <PERSON> Arden </PERSON> from the drug maker <ORGANIZATION> Eli </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lilly </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> for about $ 700 million in late 1987. Combined sales of 