<TEXT>
 Stock prices pushed ahead today, extending the advance that carried the market to new post-crash highs on Wednesday. Analysts said some traders had grown leery of chasing after stocks following the market's latest rally, which produced gains in each of the first seven trading days in July. But Wall Streeters were looking ahead optimistically to several economic reports due from the government on Friday, including monthly statistics on industrial production and the producer price index of finished goods. The figures are expected to provide further confirmation that economic growth is slowing, fulfilling a primary goal of the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reserve </ORGANIZATION>'s credit policy. Investors will give especially close scrutiny to the report on producer prices which, if it lives up to its advance billing, will show a slackening of inflationary pressures.
