<HEAD>Group Leading 3-Year-Old GE Boycott Claims It's Bruised Company's
Business</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An antinuclear group that has led a <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electric </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> boycott for three years released figures Thursday aimed at showing the campaign has cost the corporate giant $ 50.6 million in lost business. GE rejected the claims. The group <ORGANIZATION> INFACT </ORGANIZATION> based the calculation on the number of people whom it said have joined the boycott in an attempt to drive GE and other defense contractors out of the nuclear weapons industry. `` GE wants you to think it brings good things to life,'' said <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> <PERSON> Cole </PERSON>, executive director of the group. `` It also brings death and destruction. We think that's got to be stopped.'' INFACT stands for <ORGANIZATION> Infant </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Formula </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Action </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Coalition </ORGANIZATION>. The Boston-based group organized a boycott of the <ORGANIZATION> Nestle </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> a decade ago to stop that company from selling what <ORGANIZATION> INFACT </ORGANIZATION> said was unsafe powdered baby's milk. The group switched to the GE boycott in July 1986 and has claimed widespread success. By <ORGANIZATION> INFACT </ORGANIZATION>'s calculations, at least 2.53 million people worldwide have stopped buying GE products because of the boycott, resulting in lost revenue to the company of $ 25.32 million in heavily populated areas of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and an equal amount elsewhere. GE spokesman <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Jamison </PERSON> rejected <ORGANIZATION> INFACT </ORGANIZATION>'s assertions. `` Anybody can claim anything,'' <PERSON> Jamison </PERSON> said. `` The facts of the matter are, since 1985 GE revenues are up 56 percent from $ 32 billion to $ 50 billion. Earnings are up 49 percent. Also during that time, market share has increased in all GE consumer businesses. These are facts which are reported in our annual report. They speak for themselves.'' GE, based in <LOCATION> Fairfield </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Conn. </LOCATION>, makes products ranging from dishwashers to jet engines to high-tech medical equipment. It is one of the nation's leading defense contractors and the fifth-largest <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> industrial concern. The company also owns the <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> television network and a controlling interest in <ORGANIZATION> Kidder </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Peabody </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, a large Wall Street investment firm. INFACT has targeted <ORGANIZATION> GE </ORGANIZATION> because of what it calls `` the company's extensive involvement in the production and promotion of nuclear weaons and the trail of radioactive and toxic waste the company's nuclear weapons work leaves behind <PERSON> Jamison </PERSON> said `` <ORGANIZATION> INFACT </ORGANIZATION>'s goal is unilateral disarmament. We want peace every bit as much as INFACT does. But along with a majority of the <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> people, <ORGANIZATION> GE </ORGANIZATION> believes it can be assured only by a strong national defense.''
