<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A House-Senate conference trying to craft a savings and loan bailout bill adjourned Thursday night after 5 -LCB- hours of bitter and fruitless debate over how to proceed on a <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> compromise proposal. Treasury Secretary <PERSON> Nicholas </PERSON> <PERSON> F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Brady </PERSON> issued a statement that the administration would `` strongly support'' the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> offer, although he said he wanted to review the details. Sen. <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> W. </PERSON> <PERSON> Riegle </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>, D-Mich., the leader of the five-member <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> team, suprised many <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> members by starting the session with a <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> offer for a comprehensive compromise and asking them to consider it overnight or over the weekend But the huge, 94-member <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> delegation was unable to respond because its leader, Rep. <PERSON> Henry </PERSON> <PERSON> B. </PERSON> <PERSON> Gonzalez </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Texas </LOCATION>, has divided the delegation into platoons of between 20 and 30 members, each with jurisdiction over part of the bill. House delegates responded to <PERSON> Riegle </PERSON> by voting to put the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> offer aside and proceeded to try to tackle the massive S & amp; L bill issue by issue as senators sat, rolling their eyes. The <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> side made proposals on capital standards and funding, essentially mirroring the original <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> bill, but the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> refused to consider them. At the end of the session shortly after 8 p.m., the only thing the two sides could agree on was a motion to meet at 10 a.m. Friday and try again. <PERSON> Riegle </PERSON>, explaining that each position in the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> offer was `` cr